We went here this evening and it was a LOT smaller than it looks online. Order “to go” if you don’t want to have to eat with your coat on. There are only three tables so you’ll constantly get the draft of people walking in and out.  They don’t have a variety of buns and  I’m allergic to sesame seeds so I asked for two bottom buns...They charged me an extra dollar because they said that they were losing a bun and I had to pay for it. (lost a star on that one for underwhelming customer service).  Our burgers were hard and over cooked. If you’re looking for the type of burgers your mom would make you when she refused to stop for fast gifs and said “We have McDonalds ah home”, then made you one of those little rock hard bootleg burgers between two pieces of white bread, GO HERE. If not, make your own....They LOOK appetizing though!
